@finlaymh What is statically analizalbe, look at code:
```
const result = await import("./foo.js");
```

`./foo.js` is string, it means we don't need to evaluate other variables or context, just parse file -> get string -> search file and bundle it.

You have:
```js
let url = new URL("./decompWorker.js", import.meta.url);
console.log("url", url);
const worker = new window.Worker(url);
```

`url` is variables and we don't know value (more complex example - you get variable from `window` or another global object, and we don't know it, evaluation can be hard or impossible).

Just change your code to:
```js
const worker = new Worker(new URL("./decompWorker.js", import.meta.url));
```

